reviewText: Youbetcha, a new cult classic! They're drinking Summit and racing around the old bridges of Minneapolis and St. Paul in this action film.  The Cohen brothers are probably still wishing they had done this one. We'll be looking forward to more from Travis Milloy.

This movie is indeed in my top 3 best movies ever made. The acting is superb, the action and comedy is non-stop grabbing. The only part that threw me off was the random shot of two kids on bikes near the end of the film, was there a reason for this shot? I think there names were Rusty and Ryan, great actors with potential. I give this movie a 10 out of 10.
Don't miss this one. This movie should have been a blockbuster!  Very intense with great story line. This movie deserves a sequel.
